schooner capital menu founded in  schooner capital is a bostonbased private investment firm engaged in venture capital growth equity public securities and alternative assets we have no outside limited partners and approach all investments with a longterm perspective vin ryan  schooner capital menu vin ryan mia becze rachel billings peter binas antonio cienfuegos jon corbett jake fiechter orhan gazelle ted henderson katharine leal steve maiocco brian rodgers lou stathis scott yaphe vin ryan vin is founder and chairman of schooner a firm which he started in  and has managed for four decades he serves as a director of iron mountain a  billion global records management company which he purchased and grew from a single storage site a former director of continental cablevision where he invested and served on the board for more than two decades until the company was sold in  and a founder of both national hydro and arch mobile communications in addition he has served on numerous boards of schooner investments over the decades in  vin created the schooner foundation which supports a number of notforprofit causes globally with a particular emphasis on human rights vin served as a director of the marine biological laboratory the isabella stewart gardner museum physicians for human rights and survivor corps formerly landmine survivors network he also chairs the advisory board of the carr center at harvard university’s kennedy school of government vin is a graduate of boston university about us  schooner capital menu about us we view patience – a long investment horizon – as fundamental we value independent judgment and support it with a collegial atmosphere among our experienced group of professionals in all of our efforts we take care to build longterm relationships based on principle and trust we are active investors in private and public growth companies across sectors favoring recurring revenue capital efficiency and durable competitive advantage our permanent capital base allows us to respond to special situations without mandate constraints or fundraising concern we also invest capital on occasion through independent managers relying on the domain knowledge and personal character of these managers where we cannot effectively do so ourselves our alternative assets are concentrated in emerging and frontier markets though we invest in targeted strategies globally our profits directly support the schooner foundation which is actively involved in human rights causes around the world direct investments  schooner capital menu direct investments our firm invests in private companies across stage and sector in private and public markets we focus on quality of management and longterm growth prospects favoring companies with recurring revenue capital efficiency and protective moats we are drawn to innovative andor contrarian thinking with an affinity for neglected corners of markets we place a high premium on being able to respond to special situations without mandate constraints or fundraising concern most importantly we invest in people we trust and we have a long track record of vigorous support of our partners during moments of difficulty selected investments selected investments zixi wwwzixicom broadcastquality live video over unmanaged ip networks close selected investments indostar wwwindostarcapitalcom wholesale corporate credit in india close selected investments srs medical wwwsrsmedicalcom men’s pelvic health medical devices close selected investments seventh generation wwwseventhgenerationcom environmentallyresponsible household products sold to unilever close selected investments topokine therapeutics wwwtopokinetherapeuticscom noninvasive therapies for medical aesthetics sold to allergan close selected investments best doctors wwwbestdoctorscom disruptive medical management company improving quality of care via insurance products and employee benefit programs sold to a private equity buyer close selected investments orthocare in